This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with zero-shot learning using generative models for visual recognition. It also involves the use of semantic descriptions and classifiers, which are common techniques in computer vision. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) as the generative model. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the ability of machines to recognize visual objects without prior training. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with the use of semantic descriptions to generate visual samples. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with the recognition of visual objects using generative models and semantic descriptions.
